	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>letter to sony</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#131619" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Hey all, take a look and let me know what you think. I'm going to sent this off to sony soon and wanted an opinion or too.<br />
<br />
note: my spelling and gramar sucks and will be checked before its send, so no need to nitpick on that.<br />
<br />
just edited the message to add changes to the agressive, defensive and evasive disc's as well as changing the timer grouping for all the disciplines.<br />
<br />
Cartolis<br />
<br />
<br />
Hi guys and gals,<br />
 First let me say that I have played on and off for 2 years and my overall experience has been a good one.<br />
<br />
On to my specific reason for dropping you this line. On the topic of warriors there is much discussion in terms of balance. currently there are alot of players that see warriors as second rate tanks due to our inability to hold agro if someone else &quot;wants&quot; it. Now you may be wondering why I put wants in quotes. I did that because anyone with a mana bar can yank agro off a warrior almost at will. <br />
 <br />
 The reason that i see this as a design flaw and not a player interaction issue is that warriors have no way to counter it on a regular basis. with the current setup without blowing a disc, a proc going off or having the aa's for the area effect taunt(which is also on a timer).  As I am sure you already know there are alot of people out there that do not understand how to play their class in a way that allows for agro management.  This puts a warrior in a possition where we cannot do the job that our class was designed unless the people we are playing with are top notch. Sadly that is rarely the case as people have gotten spoiled by Pallys and Shadowknights nearly unshakable agro management spells. There are several changes that would allow the warriors to once again become the meatsheilds that we were ment to be.<br />
<br />
My first suggestion would be to add a second disciplne to the level 30 tier. this discipline should increase the hate generated by each swing. you could have it work like a stunless enraging blow proc that would add hate that scaled up as the warrior leveled.  for instance say the ability had a 15 min timer with a 14 min reuse clock and at level 30 increased hate by 10 for every swing and increase by 5 points per level to 65. that would put the discipline well under some of the uber eb weapons allowing them to remain popular while still allowing some of the more casual warriors that either dont have a guild or the time to raid the ability to play a warrior and still be effective. In addition to this please seperate this discipline from the normal disciplines so that you could use it and still have the ability to use the others as well.<br />
<br />
Another thing would be to change the disciplines evasive, aggressive and defensive to styles instead of disciplines. that would allow them to be used anytime. after all a warrior should be able to fight on the defensive or even aggressively more than every 18 minuits.<br />
<br />
<br />
 To my mind the role of a warrior is to take damage, keep the mob focused on one person and do some damage in the process. We are not suppose to be the damage dealers that monks or rangers arre, nor are we suppose to have spells like a paladin or shadownight. For the warrior it all comes down to skill and gear. The skill aspect is determined for you to a large extent by the game and aside from practcing the skills to get them up there is little else involved. <br />
<br />
Gear is a whole diffrent animal. The change I would like to see here is a series of quests that a warrior can do every 5-10 levels to get some medium quality armor and weapons. If implemented correctly these quests could be added for all the classes allowing all of the players of this game (specifically the more casual players) to feel a better sense of immersion. Make the armor better than random dropped stuff but less powerfull than boss mob loot doing the same for the weapons. My only other point would be to balance the quests so that they can be done with no more than 3 people. that way thoes of us that have a hard time getting a group can still do the quests.<br />
<br />
Thats about it for now. I hope that you will take My suggestions into concideration. Thank you for your time, <br />
Cartolis</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
