		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<i>Originally posted by jaxxym </i><br />
<b>The issue I see here is that your suggestion, while interesting, does not go to the heart of the problem, which is that war aggro holding ability is completely RNG-dependent (taunt, proc), whereas pally/sk aggro holding ability is reliable and spell based. Adding another disc (with reuse time that makes it useless for half or more of all encounters much like AE taunt) is not going to put war aggro on par with the spell-based aggro pallies and SKs get. <br />
<br />
Let's look at it from the perspective of the group seeking tank in a tier 2 or better xps group. If your disc is now available, the group knows that you will be able to generate more hate for, say, 15 minutes then you did before, but does that mean you can grab the mob almost immediately when it makes a run for the chanter when their slow is resisted, like a pally can? Or are you suggesting that the war generate enough hate with the new disc that a chanter's tash/slow would not be rise to the level of making the mob hate them more? And once that disc goes down, we are as useless as we are now. Pallies and SKs, on the other hand, still consistently hold aggro throughout all encounters. Ergo, pallies/SKs still remain the far preferred tank - and for good reason.<br />
<br />
Another thing it does not address - the problem of war aggro can be mitigated by a group that holds off on aggro generating spells for a period to allow the war to build aggro. In the case of your disc, this practice would still need to be observed - only casters would not need to wait quite as long. But the basic issue is that with pallies/SKs, casters don't need to wait at all since hybrids can grab back aggro with reliable spells instead of praying to the almighty RNG, and this disc does nothing to change that dynamic.<br />
<br />
I applaud your efforts Cart, and am glad to see the effort to brainstorm, but in this case even if SOE implements your suggested disc, I just don't see how that will change anything in high end xp groups, which is where the problem is most evident. </b>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> <br />
<br />
jaxxym, <br />
While I agree that having it on a timer like the current ones would limit its usefullness, I might not have been clear on what I meant. the way I had described it the disc it would be active for 15 min a shot. the reuse timer would be only 14 min long allowing for the warrior to have it up when needed, and off when not needed.  on the topic of burst agro from trigger happy casters there really isint much they can do there. if they gave us the ability to hold agro no matter what it would trivialise so much of the content that actually requires planning. <br />
<br />
I agree that it would not fix the issue of people jumping the gun, but the only thing that will fix that is knowledge. all the gear and disciplines in the world wont make some idiot who cant keep from nukeing early better.<br />
<br />
I know that this wont fix it all, but I think that it would really help us keep agro alot better.</div>
