		<div>Its usually a 2 part job.<br />
When i see the 'A_mob_01 is slowed/yawns....' message from the spell (not the hotkeyed message the slower might or might not have) and hit my taunt hotkey, chances are rather good it wont look at a_slower_01 regardless what weapons i use(it is still the RNG though).<br />
The moment eb weapons proc i wont even need to hit taunt to make sure (sitting agro is a completely different matter though).<br />
What i cannot see is what kind of spell used when casted and i will not see resists (unless mob turns toward caster after resist, so its obvious).<br />
Problems only start when your debuffer/slower casts from halfway across the zone and the mob runs out of taunt range faster than you hit taunt or after you successfully get agro back after the slow, another caster lands a crit nuke (assumed its at the start of the fight).<br />
Chance is high you will loose one attempt to taunt then right at the start (you are too far away....) and have to wait 6 seconds for another attempt that might succeed or not and loose dps to generate agro while dots/nukes keep piling in.</div>
