</div> <br />
<br />
That is exactly the issue. the real problem here is that we have hybrids that can do our job better than we can in most cases, raid being the exception.(even there there are problems)<br />
<br />
with the proper testing and tweaking this disc could even it out, and with the changes aggressive, defensive and evasive that i mentioned (making them styles not disciplines so they could be activated at will, and stack with a currently active discipline) it might be enough to balance things out.<br />
<br />
there would still be a small period in which people would need to wait for agro building. the diffrence would be that instead of having to wait for 2 bubbles of life to be gone you could go sooner AND tanks would be less dependant on the random number generator for agro.  Basically instead of having to pray for a proc or taunt sticking every successful swing would generate an agro increase.<br />
<br />
this would all be dependant on them testing it against the hybrids agro generation abilities though and a bad miss streak would still cause problems. The point is that without taking anything away from the other classes(nerfs are bad) and without adding some sort of &quot;spell agro&quot; to us(which i think would be silly, I dont want mana)  we are at the mercy of the RNG, gear and far too many people that cant catch a clue.<br />
<br />
this would atleast close that gap a bit.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2" style="border-right: 1px solid #181B16;">
		
		
		
		
		&nbsp;
	</td>
