				<div class="info">Posts: 172 
				</div>
				<div class="info">   </div>
				</div>														
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Hmmm much to think about.<br />
<br />
A problem as I see it is if you tune UP warriors' taunt ability further or you give them combat-styles or change more than a teeny bit about our Disciplines you make a huge impact on raiding. Potentially a massively unbalancing impact.<br />
<br />
How, on the other hand, can you tune DOWN Paladin/SK aggro from their spells? Well one suggestion would be to massively reduce the aggro generated by low level stuns. I find <b>that</b>  to be the major problem, Paladins using low level stuns for aggro. Make it so that they are forced to use their high level stuns and chew through their mana fast. This would make taking a Paladin as MT for your exp group a fair trade off. Potentially better aggro management for increased downtime while he or she meditates. <br />
<br />
Shadowknights I'm not so sure about. I don't find them so difficult or overly aggroing to be honest. If an SK goes all out for aggro they really do run out of mana fast, and even if they do its not anywhere near as hard to taunt back off them as it is with a Paladin.<br />
<br />
The thought crossed my mind to make the aggro generation of resisted spells next to nil, again with respect to SK/Paladins using low level spells that are resisted to make themselves so hated for little mana. Anyway I decided that was a terrible idea. There's many many good warrior weapons who's procs can and often are resisted and we wouldn't want to remove the aggro they generate. Hehe that's particularly important to me. My Norge`Tal's stun component is resisted in almost every PoP zone but it still generates me a whole busload of hate.<br />
<br />
Another thing that occurred to me is that Enchanters get Spell Casting Subtlety. If an enchanter in my group is tashing and slowing and crippling it can be quite tricky to get the mob off them fast but that AA helps. I have just checked and all INT casters get this as an Arch AA. I think we warriors need to go out and encourage our casters to get it. In the same way as they expect us to have AE Taunt, we should have the right to expect them to get that! More importantly though, what other class regularly debuffs? Shaman. Now most shaman are tough buggers and can take a few hits but I think that shaman should get this AA too. The only issue with them of course is that their heal spells would be affected but they could have a modified AA that only affected detrimental spells.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				Sarelin Seis`Bua<br />
Overlord, Thunder, Innoruuk
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
